729193f-a.title: Richmond: New Dorp Lane - 3rd Street
729193f-a.text:
(1)
New Dorp Lane, north side, between 4th and 3rd Streets,
showing the parochial school of the Roman Catholio Church of
Odn Lady GQueen of Peace and part of the church.
August 2, 1929
P. L. Sperr
NO REPRODUCTIONS
(2)
Another view of the school, at a later date, showing an
addition. The church appears in full. The view is west from
4th Street.
May 26, 1935
P. L. Sperr
NO REPRODUCTIONS

729728f-b.title: Richmond: 3rd Street - New Dorp Lane
729728f-b.text:
(1)
3rd Street, east side, between New Dorp Lane and Rose Ave.
(New Dorp), showing the Chiesa della Trinita, an lItalian Moravian
church. It is also known as Trinity Moravian (Italian) church.
August 2, 1929.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
(2)
The same, another view. The house on the right, adjoins the
church to the south and bears No. 130.
August 2, 1929.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
